<topic id='attribute_clinical_classification_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: CLINICAL CLASSIFICATION CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A unique clinical classification identifier for a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_coded_clinical_entry">CODED CLINICAL ENTRY</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
This could be 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS_Classification_of_Interventions_and_Procedures</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
) codes or 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/international_classification_of_diseases_(icd).asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">International_Classification_of_Diseases_(ICD)</xref>
 codes.  </p>
  <p>
See 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/clinical_coding_introduction.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Clinical Coding</xref>
 for further information about the types of 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_coded_clinical_entry">CODED CLINICAL ENTRIES</xref>
.  </p>

